      <h1 class="teal">Gun Control</h1><br>

      <hr><br>
      
      <h2 class="teal">Who should have the right to own or operate weapons, and under what circumstances?</h2><br>

      <hr><br>
      
      <h2 class="teal">Gun Rights in America Overview</h2><br>

      <p>During the Revolutionary War in America, many militia around the colonies got together and rallied against Britain. These militia felt that they needed weapons in order to fight the war effectively. Consequently, when the Bill of Rights was drafted, the Second Amendment addresses the militia&rsquo;s desire for the right to bear arms. The Second Amendment of the United States Constitution reads &ldquo;A well regulated Militia, being necessary to the security of a free State, the right of the people to keep and bear Arms, shall not be infringed.&rdquo;</p><br>

      <hr><br>
      
      <h2 class="teal">What is the controversy about?</h2><br>

      <p>The controversy nowadays surrounding gun control is about who should have the right to own and operate weapons, how easy it should be to obtain those weapons, and what weapons should be readily accessible, if any.</p><br>
      
